I don't believe that there is a mail forwarding requirement.  The basic
requirement for owning a domain is that you provide servers for it and
register with your parent.  Providing servers can mean finding a proxy
to do it since there is no necessary tie between a domain and the
location or names of the servers for the domain.

The MX only domain is just one minimal set of data for occupants of a
domain.  I could imagine a domain populated with terminal servers which
did TELNET only.

Of course, you can reduce this to a moot issue if the servers have no
information of any sort, but I can't think of any reason for this other
than speculation a la southern California real estate.

paul

